package spark\.gensim\.phraser\.contingency

import spark\.gensim\.phraser\.Vocab

/\*
"""
 contingency table of a bigram word\:
 w1 \~w1
 \-\-\-\-\-\- \-\-\-\-\-\-
 w2 \| n_ii \| n_oi \| \= n_xi
 \-\-\-\-\-\- \-\-\-\-\-\-
 \~w2 \| n_io \| n_oo \|
 \-\-\-\-\-\- \-\-\-\-\-\-
 \= n_ix TOTAL \= n_xx

 The letter i in the suffix refers to the appearance of the word in question\,
 while x indicates the appearance of any word\. Thus\, for example\:\:
 n_ii counts \(w1\, w2\)\, i\.e\. the bigram being scored
 n_ix counts \(w1\, \*\)
 n_xi counts \(\*\, w2\)
 n_xx counts \(\*\, \*\)\, i\.e\. any bigram
 """
 \*/
class BigramContingencyTableType \{ \}

 object BigramContingencyTableType extends ContingencyTableType \{

 override def contingency\(marginals\: Seq\[Int\]\) \= \?\?\?

 override def marginals\(contingencies\: Seq\[Int\]\) \= \?\?\?

 /\*\*
 \* \@param vocab corpus
 \* \@param word bigram word to compute marginal for
 \* \@return n_ii\, \(n_ix\, n_xi\)\, n_xx
 \*/
 override def marginals\(vocab\: Vocab\, word\: String\) \= Seq\[Int\] \{
 val ngrams \= word\.split\(vocab\.delimiter\)
 val isBigram \= ngrams\.size \=\= 2
 if\(isBigram\) \{
 val word1 \= ngrams\(0\)
 val word2 \= ngrams\(1\)

 val n_ii \= vocab\.wordCounts\.getOrElse\(word\, 0\)

 var n_ix \= 0
 var n_xi \= 0
 var n_xx \= 0
 vocab\.wordCounts\.map\( wordCount \=\> \{
 val word \= wordCount\._1
 val count \= wordCount\._2
 val isBigram \= Vocab\.isBigram\(word\, vocab\.delimiter\)
 if\(isBigram\) \{
 n_xx \= n_xx \+ count
 n_ix \= if\(word\.startsWith\(word1 \+ vocab\.delimiter\)\) n_ix \+ count else n_ix
 n_xi \= if\(word\.endsWith\(vocab\.delimiter \+ word2\)\) n_xi \+ count else n_xi
 \}
 \}\)

 Seq\(n_ii\, n_ix\, n_xi\, n_xx\)
 \}
 null
 \}
 \}
